%% WYVERN-E 4.0 — MOTOR-ejection recovery via bypass tube (no CO2, no pyro bay, no FC actuation)
flowchart TD
    B[Burnout t=3.45 s] --> C[Coast; TVC neutral; FC logs only]
    C --> A[Apogee ~6.8 s]
    A --> E[F15-4 ejection charge fires t~7.5 s]
    E --> TU[Gas -> solid-walled bypass tube -> PAST sealed FC bay]
    TU --> P[Recovery bay pressurizes ~140 kPa vs 14-41 kPa release]
    P --> N[Friction-fit nose releases -> 18 in chute + Nomex -> ~6 m/s]
